OL,7,F"We've got to fight for our children
OL,8,Fbecause they can't do it themselves,"
OL,9,FAlfie's mother, Natalie, said. "We've
OL,10,Fgot to be their voice, and I just
OL,11,Fthink it's disgusting they are cutting
OL,12,Fthe service for disabled children.
OL,14,F"It's unfair, it's really unfair for
OL,15,Fthe children - it's their future."
OL,17,FMia's mother, Lynne, added: "I totally
OL,18,Funderstand the council has to make
OL,19,Fsavings somewhere but why take it away
OL,20,Ffrom the vulnerable children? It
OL,21,Fshouldn't be happening."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/14
